verses.roman:
jagannāthera choṭa-baḍa yata bhakta-gaṇa
nija nija uttama-bhoga kare samarpaṇa

synonyms: jagannāthera—of Lord Jagannātha; choṭa—neophyte; baḍa—advanced; yata—all; bhakta-gaṇa—devotees; nija nija—personally cooked; uttama-bhoga—firstclass food; kare—do; samarpaṇa—offering.
translation: All kinds of devotees of Lord Jagannātha-from neophytes to the most advanced-offered their best cooked food to the Lord.
